    <title>Privacy Policy - Elkably</title>
    <style>
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, sans-serif;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f0f0f 0%, #1a1a2e 50%, #16213e 100%);
            min-height: 100vh;
            color: #e0e0e0;
            line-height: 1.7;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 40px 24px;
        }

        header {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 48px;
            padding-bottom: 32px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(220, 53, 69, 0.3);
        }

        .logo {
            width: 80px;
            height: 80px;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #dc3545 0%, #ff6b6b 100%);
            border-radius: 16px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            margin: 0 auto 24px;
            box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(220, 53, 69, 0.3);
        }

        .logo span {
            color: white;
            font-size: 36px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        h1 {
            color: #ffffff;
            font-size: 32px;
            font-weight: 600;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }

        .subtitle {
            color: #dc3545;
            font-size: 16px;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }

        .last-updated {
            color: #888;
            font-size: 14px;
        }

        section {
            background: rgba(30, 30, 46, 0.6);
            border-radius: 16px;
            padding: 28px;
            margin-bottom: 24px;
            border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
            backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
        }

        h2 {
            color: #dc3545;
            font-size: 20px;
            font-weight: 600;
            margin-bottom: 16px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 12px;
        }

        h2::before {
            content: '';
            width: 4px;
            height: 24px;
            background: linear-gradient(180deg, #dc3545 0%, #ff6b6b 100%);
            border-radius: 2px;
        }

        p {
            color: #c0c0c0;
            margin-bottom: 16px;
        }

        ul {
            list-style: none;
            padding-left: 0;
        }

        li {
            color: #c0c0c0;
            padding: 10px 0;
            padding-left: 28px;
            position: relative;
            border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
        }

        li:last-child {
            border-bottom: none;
        }

        li::before {
            content: '✓';
            position: absolute;
            left: 0;
            color: #dc3545;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .highlight-box {
            background: rgba(220, 53, 69, 0.1);
            border-left: 4px solid #dc3545;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }

        .highlight-box p {
            margin: 0;
            color: #e0e0e0;
        }

        .contact-info {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(220, 53, 69, 0.15) 0%, rgba(255, 107, 107, 0.1) 100%);
            border-radius: 12px;
            padding: 24px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .contact-info h3 {
            color: #ffffff;
            font-size: 18px;
            margin-bottom: 16px;
        }

        .contact-item {
            color: #dc3545;
            font-size: 16px;
            margin: 8px 0;
        }

        footer {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 32px 0;
            color: #666;
            font-size: 14px;
            border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
            margin-top: 48px;
        }

        footer span {
            color: #dc3545;
        }

        @media (max-width: 600px) {
            .container {
                padding: 24px 16px;
            }

            h1 {
                font-size: 26px;
            }

            section {
                padding: 20px;
            }

            h2 {
                font-size: 18px;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <div class="logo">
                <span>E</span>
            </div>
            <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p class="subtitle">Elkably - Student Tracking Platform</p>
            <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: December 24, 2025</p>
        </header>

        <section>
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>Welcome to Elkably. We are committed to protecting the privacy of parents, students, and all users of our Student Tracking Platform. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application.</p>
            <p>By using Elkably, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
            <p>We collect information necessary to provide our educational tracking services:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Phone number, email address, and password for parent and student portal access</li>
                <li><strong>Student Information:</strong> Student name, grade level, class assignment, and student ID</li>
                <li><strong>Attendance Records:</strong> Daily attendance status (present/absent) and homework completion status</li>
                <li><strong>Academic Data:</strong> Grades, exam scores, subject performance, and assignment submissions</li>
                <li><strong>Fee Information:</strong> Tuition fees, bus fees, activity fees, payment history, and due dates</li>
                <li><strong>Communication Data:</strong> Announcements, notifications, and messages from teachers</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>Elkably uses the collected information for the following purposes:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Provide real-time academic progress tracking for parents and students</li>
                <li>Send attendance alerts and absence notifications</li>
                <li>Display assignment deadlines and submission status</li>
                <li>Show grade reports and exam results</li>
                <li>Process and display fee payment information and reminders</li>
                <li>Deliver school announcements and teacher communications</li>
                <li>Enable parent-teacher meeting scheduling</li>
                <li>Improve our platform and user experience</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Data Protection</h2>
            <p>We implement appropriate security measures to protect your personal information:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Encrypted data transmission using industry-standard protocols</li>
                <li>Secure authentication with password protection</li>
                <li>Role-based access control (Parent Portal and Student Portal)</li>
                <li>Regular security audits and updates</li>
                <li>Secure data storage with access restrictions</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <p><strong>Your Security Matters:</strong> We never share your login credentials or personal data with unauthorized third parties. Your child's academic information is accessible only to authorized parents, students, and school staff.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
            <p>We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information. We may share data only in the following circumstances:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>With authorized school administrators and teachers for educational purposes</li>
                <li>When required by law or legal process</li>
                <li>To protect the rights and safety of users and the platform</li>
                <li>With your explicit consent</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Your Rights</h2>
            <p>As an Elkably user, you have the following rights:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Access:</strong> View all personal and academic data stored in your account</li>
                <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Request updates to inaccurate information</li>
                <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request account deletion through the Profile settings</li>
                <li><strong>Notification Control:</strong> Manage your notification preferences</li>
                <li><strong>Data Export:</strong> Request a copy of your data</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <p><strong>Account Deletion:</strong> You can delete your account at any time through the app. This will permanently remove your profile information, linked student data, payment history, and all notifications.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p>Elkably is designed for use by parents and students with school authorization. Student accounts are created and managed through the educational institution. We are committed to protecting children's privacy and comply with applicable regulations regarding minors' data.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Data Retention</h2>
            <p>We retain your information for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide our services. Academic records may be retained as required by educational regulations. Upon account deletion, your personal data will be permanently removed from our systems.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Updates to This Policy</h2>
            <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us:</p>
            <div class="contact-info">
                <h3>Elkably Support</h3>
                <p class="contact-item">Email: support@elkably.com</p>
                <p class="contact-item">App: Contact Support via Profile Settings</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <footer>
            <p><span>Elkably Platform</span> v1.0.0</p>
            <p>© 2025 Elkably. All rights reserved.</p>
        </footer>
